# Alchemist — no unsolicited “app isn’t running” talk

## Default assumption

The user manages **local** `pnpm dev` themselves. Routine work is validated with **`pnpm verify:harsh`** or **`pnpm harshcheck`** when checks are relevant. That is **enough** for most tasks — **do not** add reminders to open a browser or confirm the site loads.

## Do **not** say (unless the user clearly asked)

- That the dev server **is not** / **may not be** running  
- To **start** / **restart** the app “to verify” a change  
- To open **localhost** / **127.0.0.1** “to make sure it works” after TS/API edits  

## Do troubleshoot dev **only when** the user asks

Examples: “won’t run”, “404”, “500”, “port in use”, “run server”, “pnpm dev fails”, “need 3000”. Then use **`pnpm dev:3000`** (auto-kill listener + bind 3000), **`pnpm fresh:3000`** (same + wipe web `.next`), **`pnpm dev`**, **`pnpm fresh`**, or **`pnpm dev:recover`** from the monorepo root and follow **`alchemist-dev-server-on-request.mdc`**.

## One-shot “make it run clean” (for the user, not for you to repeat every chat)

From repo root: **`pnpm fresh`** (alias for **`pnpm web:dev:fresh`**: clean `.next` + dev). Use the **exact** `http://127.0.0.1:PORT` line from the **cyan banner** — not a random `:3000` tab.
